<DOC><DOCNO> AP881010-0170 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-10-88 2104EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-Wildfires     10-10 0213</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Wildfires,0218</SECOND><HEAD>Arson, Gunfire, and Campfire Blamed For Three Wildfires</HEAD><DATELINE>HEMET, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Three wildfires in southern Californiaburned nearly 3,000 acres and left two firefighters injured Monday.   The fires were blamed on arson, a poorly tended campfire andsparks from target practice ricochets. Dry desert winds andtemperatures topping 100 degrees aggravated firefighting efforts.   California Department of Forestry Capt. Dave Howard was caughtin a firestorm as he battled a 700-acre arson blaze about 85 milessoutheast of Los Angeles and suffered severe burns to about halfhis body, said CDF spokesman Tim Span.   Howard, one of about 200 firefighters working the blaze, wasairlifted to the burn center at Sherman Oaks Community Hospital inLos Angeles, where he was listed in critical but stable condition,Span said.   The other injury was to a female jail inmate who had been put towork on a fire line. The woman suffered burns over a small portionof her body. She was treated at the jail.   An 1,800-acre blaze in Riverside County blackened 1,800 acresafter a campfire spread to nearby brush on Sunday, Span said. Andin San Bernardino County, a 200-acre brush fire sparked Sunday bygunfire ricochets off scrap metal briefly threatened homes beforeit was encircled early Monday.</TEXT></DOC>